# Cursor rules for m3xabr-core

**Authoritative spec:** [BODY.md](mdc:BODY.md). Read it first.

**Coding lessons earned:** [LESSONS.md](mdc:LESSONS.md). Don't repeat documented mistakes.

**External tools registered:** [docs/stack/README.md](mdc:docs/stack/README.md). Every dependency has a doc; CI fails if a new one is added without one.

**Cross-tool convention:** [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md).

## Hard rules

- 7-actor pipeline is the architectural contract. Don't merge or reorder actors.
- Vendor SDK imports (anthropic, voyageai, lancedb) stay in `m3xabr_core/backends/` only.
- AUTOGEN blocks in BODY.md are off-limits to hand-edits — run `python tools/regenerate_body.py` to refresh.
- Every new dependency requires a `docs/stack/<name>.md` page. CI checks.
- Public API surface is `m3xabr_core/__init__.py` exports — don't break without a CHANGELOG entry.

## Before committing

Run: `python tools/regenerate_body.py && python tools/check_stack_in_sync.py && pytest tests/`

The pre-commit hook automates this; the CI workflow re-runs it on push.
